We can use properties of the inner product and rotation matrices.
Recall that `rotprojRM` is related to the rotation matrix `rotM`. Specifically, `rotprojRM (P 1) (P 2) (P 0) S` is the inner product of `S` with the rotation matrix applied to `P`.
Also, `p.outer P` is related to the rotation matrix applied to `P`.

Let's look at the right-hand side (RHS):
`RHS = ‚ü™w, p.outer P‚ü´`

We need to show that:
