```tactics
theorem finset_hull_linear_max {n : ‚Ñï} {V : Finset (E n)} (Vne : V.Nonempty)
    (S : E n) (hs : S ‚àà convexHull ‚Ñù V) (f : E n ‚Üí‚Çó[‚Ñù] ‚Ñù) :
    f S ‚â§ (V.image f).max' (by simp [Finset.image_nonempty]; exact Vne) := by
  have Vine : (V.image f).Nonempty := by simp [Finset.image_nonempty]; exact Vne
  have hs_orig := hs
  rw [Finset.convexHull_eq] at hs
  obtain ‚ü®w, hw1, hw2, hw3‚ü© := hs
  calc
    (f S) = (f (‚àë i ‚àà V, w i ‚Ä¢ id i)) := by rw [‚Üê hw3, Finset.centerMass_eq_of_sum_1 V id hw2]
    _       = ‚àë x ‚àà V, w x * f x := by simp
    _       ‚â§ ‚àë x ‚àà V, w x * ((V.image f).max' Vine) := f_le_max Vne w hw1 f
    _       = (‚àë x ‚àà V, w x) * ((V.image f).max' Vine) := by rw [‚Üê Finset.sum_mul]
    _       = (V.image f).max' (by simp [Finset.image_nonempty]; exact Vne) := by rw [hw2]; simp
```

This theorem `finset_hull_linear_max` states that for a nonempty finite set `V` of points in Euclidean space `E n`, and a point `S` in `E n` that is a convex combination of points in `V`, the value of a linear function `f` at `S` is less than or equal to the maximum value of `f` on the set `V`. This is a form of Jensen's inequality for linear functions.

